age Chachiyawas, District Ajmer','South Delhi','9413223809','www.rmkm.org.in','rmkm_ajm@yahoo.com',NULL,'Rajasthan Mahila Kalyan Mandal is a reputed non-governmental organisation based in Rajasthan, India working for Education and holistic development of Mentally Challenged, Autism, Cerebral Palsy and Multiple Disabled Children and also works for community development and human resource development It primarily works in Ajmer and Pali districts of Rajasthan.','390',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',80,'ngo','yes','','','Rajasthan-Mahila-Kalyan-Mandal-Sanstha','390 ',80,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(384,'NSS DTU UNIT','Delhi Technological University, New Delhi, Delhi, India','North Delhi','9958652567','https://nssdeltech.wordpress.com','dtunss@gmail.com','','The National Service Scheme (NSS) is a voluntary public service program, sponsored by the Department of Youth Affairs and Sports of the Government of India. It is aimed at developing students personality through community service, and creating a campus-community linkage. The Special Camp is an integral part of the NSS programme. The objective of this camp is to sensitise students to the realities of their country, and inspire them to work for its betterment. The NSS DTU chapter has been active since 2012.','SG','NSSDelTech','','','',' Community Development','',167,'nss','yes','','','NSS-DTU-UNIT','391 ',200,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(386,'Vision India Foundation','G-96, Saket, New Delhi','South Delhi','9958574866','http://www.visionindiafoundation.com/','aman@visionindiafoundation.com',NULL,'Vision India Foundation (VIF) is a non-profit initiative by alumni and faculty members of various IITs. VIF is a platform which offers the brightest youth of the country, avenues to participate in the modern nation building movement.','396','VisionIndiaFoundation',NULL,NULL,'',' Civil Rights & Transparency, Community Development, Education & Employment, Violence & Injustice','',114,'ngo','yes','','','Vision-India-Foundation','396 ',11,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(387,'Delhi Dialogue Commission','MB-1, Satya Sadan, Satya Marg  Madhu Limaye Marg Chanakyapuri, New Delhi','South Delhi','-','http://delhi.gov.in/wps/wcm/connect/DoIT/delhi+govt/delhi+home','ddc.delhi@gov.in',NULL,'Delhi is a microcosm of India, a melting pot of different cultures and influences. As a national capital, Delhi is also the prism through which India is seen by the world. An efficient administration, holistic development and a feeling of safety and security are absolutely necessary for Delhi . To achieve this Government of NCT of Delhi has constituted &#34;Delhi Dialogue Commission&#34; to come up with new and big ideas,identify best practices and policies from around the world and translate them into concrete recommendations to the Government of NCT of Delhi for transformative change.','108',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Community Development','',211,'ngo','yes','','http://helpiez.org/img/ngologo/387_20150325_132823.jpg','Delhi-Dialogue-Commision','398 450 188 ',1000,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(392,'NSS Hansraj College','Hansraj College, New Delhi, Delhi, India','North Delhi','-','http://www.hansrajcollege.co.in/nss.htm','rohan.ch.1995@gmail.com',NULL,'1. Health- Under this we organised &#34;blood donation camps, medical health checkup for girls in college, pink chain campaign for breast and cervical cancer.\r\n\r\n2. Environment- Under this branch NSS Hansraj conducts &#34;plantation drive and cleanliness drive&#34; in college. A plantation drive was organised in college in association with UNICEF in which Indian cricketer Suresh Raina was the chief guest.\r\n\r\n3. Education- This is the branch of NSS Hansraj which works on a daily basis. Kids of classes 1-12 from nearby slum come to college and are taught by our volunteers. This branch works under the name &#34;Padhaku&#34;.\r\n\r\n4. Disaster Management- This branch is to promote disaster management techniques among the college students and outsiders. Various initiatives like &#34;hills