 ','',108,'nss','','','','NSS-KMC','565 ',2000,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(403,'NSS Society of Lady Irwin College','Lady Irwin College, New Delhi, Delhi, India','','9654499390','','mansisheenu@gmail.com',NULL,'The National Service Scheme (NSS) was initiated by the Government of India in 1969 with the avowed intention of involving the youth in the nation-building process. It is based on the philosophy of Mahatma Gandhi. The NSS Society is to provide an essential link between the college campus and the surrounding community. Not only is it expected to arouse the social consciousness of the students and teachers alike but also to provide an avenue for personality development through community service. The society seeks to achieve communication through street plays, organizing events like blood donation camps, NDTV talk shows and eliminating the ragging.','583',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Community Development','',92,'nss','','','','NSS-Society-of-Lady-Irwin-College','583 ',200,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(404,'NSS ROTARACT CLUB OF NSIT REGENCY','Netaji Subas Institute of Technology Azad Hind Fauj Marg Sector - 3 , Dwarka , New Delhi 110075.','','9953844867, Pranjal Chugh: 9716789172',' http://www.nsitrotaract.org/','garimagupta76@gmail.com',NULL,'Rotaract Club of NSIT Regency, the official social service club in NSIT, is a Rotary sponsored club for young men and women between the ages 18 to 30. It is a part of Rotaract District 3010. Established in April 2009, currently it has more than 800 members and a dedicated Core Team. The objective of the Club is to address the social and physical needs of the community and enhance leadership and management skills of the young students by involving them in social, entrepreneurial & technical activities that aims at development of the community around us.\r\n\r\nNSIT Rotaract Club has been dynamically involved in education, skill building and community services at the slum sites, initiating collection drives, pioneering the cause related to mentally challenged children, organizing managerial activities & workshops and events, and also engaged in handing technical support like website designing, database management for some NGOâ€™s.','586',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Children & Youth, Community Development, Education & Employment, Empower Disabled, Environment, Women ','',111,'nss','','','','NSS-ROTARACT-CLUB-OF-NSIT-REGENCY','586 ',800,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(408,'Lakshyam','253/1, First Floor, Shahpur Jat, Opposite Bank of India,  New Delhi - 110049 ','East Delhi','011-26492418 095407i90002','http://www.lakshyam.co.in/index.html','support@lakshyam.co.in',NULL,'Established in 2004,&nbsp;Lakshyam&nbsp;is a social enterprise that uplifts children and women of at-risk communities through education, employment and resource mobilization. Currently functional in 11 states of&nbsp;India&nbsp;with 13 centers,&nbsp;Lakshyam&rsquo;s&nbsp;&#39;Butterfly: Child Welfare &amp; Education&#39; program offers holistic education to children, &#39;Lakshyam&nbsp;Toy Library&#39; is a need-based approach and &#39;Rooh: Awakening Women&rsquo;s Soul&#39; is designed to empower women via awareness, initiation and action..','640',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Children & Youth, Community Development, Education & Employment','',248,'ngo','','','http://helpiez.org/img/ngologo/408_20150507_160830.jpg','Lakshyam','640 ',15,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(409,'Pratham','B- 4/58, Safdarjung Enclave  2nd Floor, New Delhi-110 029','East Delhi',' (011) 26716083 / 41651638 ','http://www.pratham.org/','info@pratham.org',NULL,'Pratham is an innovative learning organization created to improve the quality of education in India. As one of the largest non-governmental organizations in the country, Pratham focuses on high-quality, low-cost, and replicable interventions to address gaps in the education system. Established in 1995 to provide education to children in the slums of Mumbai, Pratham has grown both in scope and geographical coverage.','108',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Children & Youth','',144,'ngo','','','','Pratham','',10,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(410,'People for Parity (PfP)','B-4/156, Safdurjung Enclave, 3rd Floor, New Delhi - 110 029, India','East Delhi','9560717965','peopleforparity.org','contact@peopleforparity.org',NULL,'People for Parity (PfP) is a youth-led social change organization which works with young people to help them identify, understand &amp; challenge gender based violence and discrimination in their own lives and communities. We are among the few social enterprises in the country which work with issues concerning all genders. We have conducted workshops with more than 5000 young people across 6 states till date, training several gender facilitators and witnessing numerous transformative journeys in the process. We have successfully partnered with various governmental and non-governmental bodies over the course of our work including police forces in Rajasthan and Uttarakhand, and with UNICEF as part of their End Violence Campaign in Jharkhand.\r\nOur main supporting partners include UN-Habitat in collaboration with the Narotam Sekhsaria Foundation (NSF), Pravah, Unltd Delhi, Commutiny &ndash; The Youth Collective, and RDNC Mittal Foundation, among others. People for Parity is among the 5 Indian recipients of the Global Urban Youth Fund, a UN-Habitat and NSF initiative, and among the only 22 recipients in the world.','108',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Children & Youth, Violence & Injustice, Women ','',83,'ngo','yes','','','People-for-Parity-(PfP)','727 ',5,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(411,'Bringing underprivileged children teaching projects online','-','','9013058459','','helpiezteam@gmail.com',NULL,'<p><span style=\"font-family: Questrial; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18.8181819915772px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In this campaign we intend to bring all the slum teaching projects online and give them an online platform to highlight the noble work they are doing and in the meantime, assist them in any problem they might be facing (For e.g.- Staff-crunch, lack of infrastructure, stationery,etc.)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Questrial; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18.8181819915772px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">There are two categories of teaching projects going on today-</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; list-style-type: disc; font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Registered- </span><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Which are registered as NGOs or under some NGO; are well-known throughout the social circles. Such projects are generally well-funded and see ample participation by people. For e.g.- Teach for India.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; list-style-type: disc; font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Unregistered- </span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Generally small-scale projects; individual- or a group of individuals- (like NSS society of some college) driven. Are known by only a handful of people and thus face many problems due to lack of funds, tutors and many-a-times, public support.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Our main focus is to incorporate these unregistered projects into one campaign so that help and support is available to them always to carry out their commendable work unrestrictedly.*</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Most of the people are not aware of these projects. So, our mission is to bring each and every teaching project currently being run in Delhi under our campaign and give them the right platform for people to contribute, interact and communicate.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">We will give all the projects wider outreach by giving them separate pages on our website and try to provide any and every kind of support possible.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">If possible we can even conduct exams of children who are studying in those projects and talented ones can get a chance to have their studies being sponsored.**</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">We can reach out to those places also where there is a need of these type of teaching projects but not started yet.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 30.1090888977051px; text-decoration: underline;\">Beneficiary</span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Underprivileged children who don&rsquo;t have access to proper education.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Youth who want to contribute to the upliftment of society. (Honed communication and interpersonal skills; strategy and decision-making skills; much impressive CV are some of its added benefits).</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; font-family: Questrial; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Impact</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 16px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Regular availability of </span><span style=\"font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">tutors and volunteers.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 15px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Online presence</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\"> would give them a sort of authenticity</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 16px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">Wider outreach </span><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">would result in more contribution from people. It can be in any form- Volunteering for teaching, providing a basic infrastructure setup to carry out the classes, stationery and even donations.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 16px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">And the most important of all, </span><span style=\"font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">quality education </span><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">to the kids.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-family: Questrial; font-size: 16px; line-height: 20.0727272033691px;\">We believe that access to quality education is every child&rsquo;s right (but sadly has been restricted to the privileged ones only). So it is a moral duty of everyone to contribute towards the education of the less fortunate ones. Because a chain is as strong as its weakest link and we have quite-a-many weak links to strengthen.</span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">*Our campaign will also include the registered projects too. But as mentioned earlier too, most of them already are well-off so the resources would be distributed comprehensively.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-family: georgia, serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; font-family: Questrial; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;\">**It is just a suggestion and by no means a finalised decision. We are open to such suggestions by everyone but the final undertaking will be taken after evaluating and assessing all the resources at hand.</span></p>','108',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Children & Youth','',368,'ngo','yes','http://helpiez.org/img/ngoBackImg/_20150604_071515.jpg','','Bringing-underprivileged-children-teaching-projects-online','108 ',10,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(412,'Big Brother Foundation','JMJ House, Orchard Avenue, Garden, Hiranandani Garden, Powai, Mumbai','','02267112233','http://bigbrotherfoundation.com/','reachbigbrotherfoundation@gmail.com',NULL,'<p><span style=\"color: #333333; font-family: ABeeZee; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.200000002980232px; line-height: 20px; text-align: justify;\">Set up in 2012 as a not for profit initiative, Big Brother is the passionate endeavour of social visionary Sachiin Joshi, for empowering underprivileged children and women in rural India. The committed social evangelist Raina Joshi matches his bold strides towards gifting our underprivileged citizens a better future.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','773',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Children & Youth','',32,'ngo','yes','','','Big-Brother-Foundation','',10,0,'0000-00-00','unchecked'),(413,'Annamrita','19 Jaywant Industrial Estate, 63 Tardeo Road, Mumbai, Maharashtra â€“ 400 034.','','022-23531530 ','http://annamrita.org','annamritaiskconfoodrelieffound@gmail.com',NULL,'<p>Contribute towards a good cause. Annamrita is an NGO that provides 12,00,000 meals everyday to school children across 8 states in India.</p>','826',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Children & Youth','',9,'ngo','yes','','','Annamrita','826 ',10,0,'0000-00-00','checked'),(414,'Dahij Service Organization','2-99, Ragolu,Srikakulam','','8121912855,8686159156','www.dahij.org','info@dahij.org',NULL,'<p>\"Prevention is better than Cure but so as to prevent, we need to be aware\". So we are working in creating awareness on various health aspects among school children, rural and tribal people.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This organization is founded by medicos because we felt that the sufferings of people is not just because of lack of hospital facilities alone but also due to lack of health awareness that is why we are focusing on educating people on health aspects.</p>\r\n<p>To knowmore, visit www.Dahij.org</p>','827',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' Health & Medicine','',11,'ngo','yes','','','Dahij-Service-Organization','827 ',20,0,'0000-00-00','checked');
