ir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.3800000000000001; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">â— &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Teach For India lays high emphasis on School Dress Code, Code of Conducts and a Child Protect Policy and will be very particular about adherence to the same.</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.3800000000000001; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We only have schools in north and south Delhi. </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.3800000000000001; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The deadline for the Signup is 25th May 2015 </span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.3800000000000001; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You can sign up for the internship </span><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/a/teachforindia.org/forms/d/18QfTDLXJSbwcOYuGvCrs3uVtgxRr1fHeUuxBeYVzoqc/viewform\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri; color: #0000ff; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.3800000000000001; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">All Secondary Classroom Subordinates will be awarded a TFI Internship Certificate post the internship during a small graduation ceremony.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>','New Delhi, Delhi, India','','Its an unpaid internship ',' Community Development','volunteerdelhi@teachforindia.org',' Teaching & Training, Community Engagement','Undergraduates,  Graduates, Housewife, Retired and Young Professionals , B.ed Students','1 Month ','01-07-2015','775','','','./img/cause/internbanner.jpg','2015-05-19 07:29:43','Intern,-Classroom-Subordinate-','','','checked','','2015-06-30 07:00:00',' Regular','yes','0000-00-00 00:00:00','NCR'),(101,'An on ground social leadership program while you are in College ','internship',723,0,'30','<p>If you have it in you to walk out of your comfort zones, toil in this Delhi heat,put your heart and soul towards molding the <span class=\"text_exposed_show\">lives of tiny little souls by helping them enhance their very rudimentary skill set;then this is the place for you!And with that the tremendous self evolution opportunity that awaits you here is definitely more than huge. Come in here,do the greater good,influence others and transform yourselves to influential torchbearers and social leaders!!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Application form : http://bit.ly/1K3IDDS </span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">or</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Find us at : www.prathamdelhi.org</span></p>','Delhi, India','','no',' Children & Youth, Community Development','inturn.saajha@gmail.com',' Community Engagement','Students who are willing to beat the Delhi summer heat and are willing to give back to the society.','1 month','05-06-2015','729 735 740','740 735 729 ','','./img/cause/internbanner.jpg','2015-05-24 08:51:01','An-on-ground-social-leadership-program-while-you-are-in-College-','','','checked','','2015-07-05 00:00:00',' Regular','yes','0000-00-00 00:00:00','NCR'),(102,'Applicant','internship',727,410,'Any number of people may apply','<p>PLEASE NOTE: This is a call to apply for a fellowship, not an internship. Anyone between the ages of 18-35 and a resident of Delhi is free to apply.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6px 0px; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21.466667175293px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"display: inline; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21.466667175293px;\">\r\n<p style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px; white-space: pre-wrap; color: #141823; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #1155cc;\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/PeopleForParity?fref=ts\" target=\"_blank\">People for Parity Foundation (PfP)</a>, New Delhi</strong>, in support with UN HABITAT and the Narotam Sekhsaria Foundation, is launching its special project for tackling Gender Based Violence, <strong>PRATITI</strong>, open for youth belonging to the ages of 18-30 in 5 Indian cities - Delhi, Jaipur, Bhopal. Lucknow and Patna. </span></p>\r\n<blockquote class=\"gmail_quote\" style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0.8ex; border-left-width: 1px; border-left-color: #cccccc; border-left-style: solid; padding-left: 1ex;\"><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\"><em><strong><font face=\"arial, helvetica, sans-serif\">Pratiti has been designed as a journey, an opportunity and an experience, for young, diverse and passionate individuals who desire to explore, reflect, share and learn about gender-based violence in a warm and non-judgmental environment, which will nurture and transform them into empathetic leaders for gender equality.</font></strong></em></span></blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin: 0px; white-space: pre-wrap; color: #141823; line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\">Applicants can be from any background and representative of any color of the rainbow, including people who may be straight, gay, lesbian, transsexual, transgender, hijra, survivors or even sex workers.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin: 10px 0px 0px;\"><font color=\"#141823\" face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"line-height: 19.9333343505859px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">20 participants will be selected in each city to become part of an experiential journey which will enable them to: </span></font></p>\r\n<ul style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-left: 15px;\"><font color=\"#141823\" face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><em><strong style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; color: #222222;\">&gt; Become an empathetic leader for gender equality&nbsp;</strong><br /></em></font></li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-left: 15px;\"><font color=\"#141823\" face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><em><strong style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; color: #222222;\">&gt; Use sharing, healing and facilitation as powerful tools for change&nbsp;</strong><br /></em></font></li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-left: 15px;\"><font color=\"#141823\" face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; color: #222222;\"><em>&gt; Understand what gender-based violence is and how one can challenge it</em></strong><br /></font></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin: 10px 0px 0px;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">The fellowship will take place between July-October 2015, and over the course of these 4 months, participants will involve themselves in:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin: 12pt 0in 12pt 0.75in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-left: 15px;\"><strong><font face=\"arial, helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\"><span style=\"font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\">A common launch event</span><br /></font></strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-left: 15px;\"><strong><font face=\"arial, helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\"><span style=\"font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\">An intense three-day workshop</span><br /></font></strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-left: 15px;\"><strong><font face=\"arial, helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\"><span style=\"font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\">Action projects on gender issues in their community</span><br /></font></strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-left: 15px;\"><strong><font face=\"arial, helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\"><span style=\"font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\">Regular community meetings for reflection and sharing</span><br /></font></strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-left: 15px;\"><strong><font face=\"arial, helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\"><span style=\"font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"line-height: 14.7200012207031px;\">A co-created closure and finale event which will celebrate the journey</span></font></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8000001907349px; margin: 10px 0px 0px; white-space: pre-wrap; color: #141823;\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\">30th June, 2015 is the application deadline for Delhi and Jaipur. Pratiti will </span></font><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\">not require full-time involvement from the participants nor any sort of expenditure from their side.</span> <span style=\"font-size: 12.8000001907349px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\">If you are in the 18-30 odd age group and a resident of the above-mentioned cities, you are eligible to apply.</span> <font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\"> TO APPLY, PLEASE VISIT: </span></font><a style=\"color: #3b5998; font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.9333343505859px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://peopleforparity.org/applications\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://peopleforparity.org/<wbr />applications</a> <span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\">FOR MORE DETAILS, VISIT </span><a style=\"color: #3b5998; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.9333343505859px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://peopleforparity.org/pratiti/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://peopleforparity.org/<wbr />pratiti/</a> or click on our <a style=\"color: #1155cc;\" href=\"https://www.saddahaq.com/events/human-interest/lgbt/the-pratiti-fellowship?fb_ref=Default\" target=\"_blank\">Saddahaq</a> link!   <span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.9333343505859px;\">Kindly share and spread the word. <strong>Because rainbows are beautiful</strong>!<strong> :)</strong></span></p>\r\n</div>','Delhi, India','','Expenses will be reimbursed',' Children & Youth, Community Development, Violence & Injustice, Women ','somesh.pfp@gmail.com',' Community Engagement','Anyone in the 18-35 age bracket and a resident of the 5 mentioned cities may apply','July-October 2015','01-07-2015','','','','./img/cause/internbanner.jpg','2015-06-15 13:42:59','Applicant','','','unchecked','','2015-06-30 00:00:00',' Regular','yes','0000-00-00 00:00:00',''),(103,'People for Parity (PfP)','internship',727,410,'5','<p>For all young people who are interested in identifying and challenging Gender Based Violence (GBV) in their personal, professional and social lives, People for Parity (PfP) has internships and volunteering opportunities open throughout the year. If you have the passion and committment towards creating positive social change, welcome aboard! :)</p>','Safdarjung Enclave, New Delhi, Delhi, India','','Expenses will be reimbursed',' Children & Youth, Human Rights, Violence & Injustice, Women ','somesh.pfp@gmail.com',' Multimedia & Designing, Community Engagement, Marketing & Publicity, Internet & Web Development, Operation & Logistics','Open for all ','2 months','27-07-2015','','','','./img/cause/internbanner.jpg','2015-07-16 04:49:04','People-for-Parity-(PfP)','','','unchecked','','2015-12-31 00:00:00',' Regular','yes','0000-00-00 00:00:00','');
